Here is my SUMMARY for the lesson:  Transmission Delay: The amount of time needed to place the complete data packet on the transmission medium. Transmission Time = Message size / Bandwidth  Propagation Delay: The amount of time a bit takes to go from device A to device B.  Propagation Time = Distance / Propagation speed  Queuing Delay: The third component in latency. It is the time needed for each intermediate or end device to hold the message before it can be processes.  This delay is not a fixed factor; it changes with the load imposed on the network. When there is heavy traffic on the network, the queuing time increases.  Processing Delay: The amount of time a node takes to process the sent message.  Hope that helps!
